#~C%ric$o-iA]/HNhH`B: Description Data
The default Terraria experience. World generation has no oddities. If this is active, no other seed extra can be enabled.
Creates a random selection of seeds to create interesting combos.
Generates a world that is a combination of the Drunk, Not the Bees, For the Worthy, Celebration MK 10, The Constant, No Traps, and Remix seeds.
Generates a world dominated by bee-themed biomes and bee-related items and structures.
Generates a world with both evil biomes, as well as both variants of any ore that comes in two varieties. Other world generation oddities will occur.
This seed celebrates Terraria's tenth birthday, on May 16, 2021, and generates a world that offers several unique and highly beneficial features.
This seed is part of the crossover with the game Don't Starve Together. Introduces hunger and darkness mechanics. Other world generation oddities will occur.
Increases the difficulty up one level, up to Legendary. Introduces new mechanics to further increase difficulty. Other world generation, and gameplay oddities will occur.
Generates a world with significantly more traps than normal. It also contains new traps.
Flips the usual order of player progression through biomes by having the player spawn in the central part of the underworld. Other world generation, and gameplay oddities will occur.
Generates a world with a small sky island that players spawn on. Two additional sky islands spawn on the outer edges of the world, with one of them being an island of shimmer.
Generates a world entirely painted gray.
Generates a world entirely painted negative, making all blocks, walls, and furniture a negative image of itself.
The entire world is painted with echo coating, making tiles and walls invisible.
The entire world is painted with illuminant coating, making tiles and walls appear at maximum light level, effectively giving you xray.
The entire world is underground, and there is no surface biome at all. Meteorites spawn naturally in the outer parts of the world. Mana crystals spawn naturally similar to life crystals.
Adds giant living trees that spawn frequently throughout all surface biomes. Their root tunnels extend deep into the world, well into the cavern layer.
Adds large floating islands that spawn frequently throughout the majority of the world.
Generates a world with naturally spawning graveyards, beginning the world at 7:30 PM during a blood moon.
Raises the surface layer to space height.
Makes the world constantly rain, and has unique events.
The underground cabins & ruined houses are generated with additional rooms added to their structure.
Makes the world spawn point in a location on the map.
Pairs of teleporters with pressure plates on top are scattered across the underground.
The world starts with hardmode enabled, including hardmode generation.
Generates a world with no world evils.
Generates a world with most of the surface covered in hallow.
Generates a world almost completely infected with the selected world evil.
Generates a world with most of the surface covered in glowing mushroom biomes.
Generates a world with most of the surface covered in desert.
Generates a world with large clumps of poo blocks covering the world.
Spider nests no longer spawn. If four or more other secret seeds are in effect, instead increases the amount of spider nests in the world.
Generates a world with absolutely no traps.
Generates a world where rainbows replace some generation, or add rainbows to existing generation.
Generates a world with large chasms and pits all across the surface, leading deep into the underground and cavern layers.
Generates a world as circular landmasses of varying sizes, across all layers. Mixing this seed with the mole people seed, inverts the map. Planetoids become cavities in areas of full blocks.
Generates a world where water covers most of the world until lava starts to appear in the caverns. Bubble blocks generate as air pockets covering various tunnels and trees.
Currently Unknown
Generates a world that is almost completely tundra and ice biomes.
Generates a world where pumpkins are planted randomly.
Causes the Halloween event to always be active.
Causes the Christmas event to always be active.
Turns players into vampires. Going onto the surface at daytime or is within range of sunlight inflicts several damaging debuffs until they retreat or stop the effects.
Spawns players on differing areas of the world in multiplayer depending on what team they have selected.
Generates a world with two dungeons, one on either side of the world. Every major biome is split between these two dungeons.
